ession was started\\n    60→\\tStartedAt time.Time `json:\\\"started_at\\\"`\\n    61→\\n    62→\\t// EndedAt is when the session was explicitly closed by the user.\\n    63→\\t// nil means the session is still active or was not cleanly closed.\\n    64→\\tEndedAt *time.Time `json:\\\"ended_at,omitempty\\\"`\\n    65→\\n    66→\\t// Phase is the lifecycle stage of this session (see phase.go).\\n    67→\\t// Empty means idle (backward compat with pre-state-machine files).\\n    68→\\tPhase Phase `json:\\\"phase,omitempty\\\"`\\n    69→\\n    70→\\t// TurnID is a unique identifier for the current agent turn.\\n    71→\\t// Lifecycle:\\n    72→\\t//   - Generated fresh in InitializeSession at each turn start\\n    73→\\t//   - Shared across all checkpoints within the same turn\\n    74→\\t//   - Used to correlate related checkpoints when a turn's work spans multiple commits\\n    75→\\t//   - Persists until the next InitializeSession call generates a new one\\n    76→\\tTurnID string `json:\\\"turn_id,omitempty\\\"`\\n    77→\\n    78→\\t// TurnCheckpointIDs tracks all checkpoint IDs condensed during the current turn.\\n    79→\\t// Lifecycle:\\n    80→\\t//   - Set in PostCommit when a checkpoint is condensed for an ACTIVE session\\n    81→\\t//   - Consumed in HandleTurnEnd to finalize all checkpoints with the full transcript\\n    82→\\t//   - Cleared in HandleTurnEnd after finalization completes\\n    83→\\t//   - Cleared in InitializeSession when a new prompt starts\\n    84→\\t//   - Cleared when session is reset (ResetSession deletes the state file entirely)\\n    85→\\tTurnCheckpointIDs []string `json:\\\"turn_checkpoint_ids,omitempty\\\"`\\n    86→\\n    87→\\t// LastInteractionTime is updated on agent-interaction events (TurnStart,\\n    88→\\t// TurnEnd, SessionStop, Compaction) but NOT on git commit hooks.\\n    89→\\t// Used for stale session detection in \\\"entire doctor\\\".\\n    90→\\tLastInteractionTime *time.Time `json:\\\"last_interaction_time,omit